{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1773", "title": "Pharmacy benefit managers.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Pharmacybenefitmanagers"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law, the Knox-Keene Health Care Service Plan Act of 1975, provides for the licensure and regulation of health care service plans by the Department of Managed Health Care, and makes a willful violation of the act a crime. Existing law provides for the regulation of health insurers by the Department of Insurance. Existing law requires a pharmacy benefit manager contracting with a health care service plan or health insurer to secure a license from the Department of Managed Health Care on or after January 1, 2027, or the date on which the department has established the licensure process, whichever is later.\n\nThis bill would require the department to maintain a public internet website displaying specified information for each licensed pharmacy benefit manager, including, among other things, the legal name, license number, and license expiration date."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Medi-Cal: prerelease services for inmates."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1773"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-09", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 12.", "date": "2026-02-10", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on HEALTH.", "date": "2026-03-16", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on HEALTH.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee chair, 